// QuestionPanel
// Slide-in overlay panel that presents Claude's current question to the user.
// Implements a focus trap (Tab/Shift+Tab cycles within the panel) and Escape
// to dismiss. Shows success or error banners from the submit state, then
// delegates question rendering to QuestionRenderer.
// Renders nothing when there is no currentQuestion.

FUNCTION QuestionPanel() -> JSX                                        EXPORT
  CALLS: QuestionRenderer (QuestionRenderer)
  Reads currentQuestion, submitState, dismissQuestion, submitResponse from
  questionStore.
  Keyboard handler: Escape calls dismissQuestion; Tab traps focus within
  panel focusable elements.
  On question change: re-collects focusable elements and focuses the first.
  Renders: semi-transparent backdrop (click to dismiss) + right-side panel.
  Panel contains: header ("Claude is asking..." + optional context + close
  button), scrollable content area, footer with ESC hint.
  Content area: shows error banner if submitState.error; shows success banner
  if submitState.success; otherwise renders QuestionRenderer.

---

FUNCTION handleDismiss() -> void
  Calls dismissQuestion().

---

FUNCTION handleAction(actionId, payload) -> void
  Calls submitResponse with questionId, answer (serialized payload), and
  current timestamp.
  Logs errors to console but does not surface them (QuestionPanel shows
  submitState.error instead).
